@node "CanDo_License_New" "CanDo v2.5x License changes..."
@toc "CanDo_Main"
CanDo 2.5 Revised Applications Distribution Policy

   With the introduction of CanDo Version 2.5, Inovatronics is no longer
distributing the DeckBrowser program. CanDo's Binder utilities no longer
give you the ability to create freely distributable applications that
include a complete runtime system. As before, you may still bind your
program with DeckRunner to inhibit CanDo's ability to load and edit that
deck. Decks and bound decks may still be freely distributed; however, only
users that have CanDo will be able to run these applications. Commercial
developers that want to sell or distribute their finished software should
contact Inovatronics regarding licensing of the CanDo runtime library.
License fees are reasonable and agreements are available for review.


@{fg highlight}NOTE:@{fg text} The CanDo.Library file is copyrighted software and IS NOT freely
      distributable.

@endnode

